    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-03-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-03-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/362: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-19T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Department’s March 18, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department suggested that first four points of Department’s March 17, 5 p.m. be
                    included in President Estrada Cabrera’s proclamation. Department has no
                    objection to the proclamation containing, after the third point, an explanation
                    to the effect that crimes punishable by the laws of the country are not to be
                    considered “political reasons”.</p>
                <p>The Department does not insist on the inclusion of the fourth point in the
                    proclamation but will be content with a verbal assurance from President Estrada
                    Cabrera that prisoners will not be subjected to torture or flogging.</p>
                <p>These conclusions have been come to after a conference with Doctor Toledo
                        Herrarte,<note n="7" xml:id="d626fn7">Chief of the Guatemalan Special
                        Mission to the United States.</note> and the Minister of Guatemala, who will
                    telegraph their government accordingly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
